         "id": "SECTION_images",
         "text": [
            {
               "text": "### Images from Ashmolean\n\nThese images are copyright for Ashmolean and allowed to be used according to the license determined by them.\n\nTo visualize all images, use the left and right arrows on the slide below.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgEA\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgEA', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Fragment of the epic <i>Enmerkar and the lord of Aratta</i>. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite0>).</div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgHarappaW\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgHarappaW', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Harappa Seal. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite1>). Shared under the <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/\" target=\"_blank\">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>History: Cradles of civilization (Parte II) (<htcite4>)</li><li>Understanding Texts: The Writing System - More than just a tool for daily use, the writing system is a milestone that allows us to divide human history into prehistory and recorded events. (<htcite5>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">3 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgS\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgS', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Estatuillas of the Sixth Dynasty. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite2>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Myths and Believes: What is the extent of the impact of the flood? (<htcite6>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">4 / 4</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgKL\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgKL', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Sumerian King List. © Ashmolean Museum, University of Oxford (<htcite3>).</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>History: Cradles of civilization (Part I) - While humanity originated in Africa, the first civilizations emerged in various regions around the world, such as Mesopotamia, the Andes, and Mesoamerica. (<htcite7>)</li><li>History: Sumerian King List - This text compiles all references to the Sumerian King List available in <i>History Tracers</i>. (<htcite8>)</li><li>History: What is time? - In this text, we begin to explore one of the most important variables in both history and physics—time. (<htcite9>)</li><li>Understanding Texts: Fractionating Texts - In this text, we delve deeper into the concept of groups and introduce fractions as an additional tool for understanding texts. (<htcite10>)</li><li>Understanding Texts: The Writing System - More than just a tool for daily use, the writing system is a milestone that allows us to divide human history into prehistory and recorded events. (<htcite5>)</li><li>Myths and Believes: Is it possible to live in the sky? Is the Earth flat? (<htcite6>)</li><li>Myths and Believes: What is the extent of the impact of the flood? (<htcite6>)</li></ul></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
